The Vice President, Joe Biden, released a statement expressing his condolences on the passing of Sarah Brady, wife of Jim Brady. He remembers speaking with her last October and admiring their grace, dignity, and determination. Together, they faced tragedy and turned it into action, working together to make America a safer place. They fought for bipartisan consensus on gun control measures, including the Brady Bill, which has saved countless lives. Biden honors their legacy and sends his condolences to the Brady family.